news.title: Delhi: CBI registers FIR against Signature View builders, officials
news.para: The CBI has initiated an investigation into alleged criminal conspiracy and compromised construction quality at Signature View Apartments in Mukherjee Nagar, Delhi. The FIR names builders and DDA officials following a complaint by DDA, highlighting substandard materials used in the construction of 224 HIG and 112 MIG flats. Consequently, the buildings were deemed unsafe for habitation within a decade.

news.title: Gurugram bar association seeks probe into judge’s order in realty case five days before retirement
news.para: The Gurgaon bar association has accused a recently retired city court judge of favouring a leading developer in a land case, alleging judicial impropriety and external influence. The bar claims the judge expedited proceedings just before retirement, raising concerns about impartiality.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines Sunrise Infra Properties for illegal farm plot sales
news.para: Telangana RERA has penalized Sunrise Infra Properties Rs 25.8 lakh for illegally advertising and selling plots in their Siri Vanam project without required approvals. The company marketed agricultural land as farm plots, subdividing them without proper authorization. TG RERA has restrained the company from further sales until approvals are secured and directed them to register the project.

news.title: Haryana RERA orders Sarv Realtors to refund buyer's money for delayed flat
news.para: HRera directed Sarv Realtors to refund ₹41.6 lakh with 11.1% interest to a couple who booked a 3BHK flat in Supertech Hues in 2014, as the realtor failed to deliver possession by the agreed deadline. The authority dismissed the developer's reasons for the delay, citing that the possession date lapsed long before the pandemic and insolvency proceedings.

news.title: Hero Realty buys 8.71 acres of land in Mohali for ₹262.75 crore
news.para: Hero Realty, through Vikas Parks Pvt. Ltd., has acquired 8.71 acres in Mohali's Sector 99 for Rs 262.75 crore via GMADA auction, planning a new residential project. Building on the success of its Hero Homes project in Sector 88 Mohali, the company aims to strengthen its presence in the Tricity market.

news.title: BNP Paribas India leases 1.45 lakh sq ft office space in Thane
news.para: BNP Paribas India Solutions has leased 145,000 sq ft of office space in Thane, marking a significant expansion outside Mumbai's core business districts. This five-year lease reflects a trend of companies seeking cost-effective alternatives to prime locations like BKC. The deal highlights the continued demand for commercial space in India despite global economic uncertainties.

news.title: Hongkong Land to sell MCL Land to Malaysia's Sunway for $578 million
news.para: Hongkong Land has sold its MCL Land to Sunway Group. The deal is worth S$739 million. Hongkong Land will use the funds to boost its balance sheet. They will also increase share buybacks. The company is shifting away from residential development. They want to focus on premium commercial properties. Sunway aims to strengthen its property portfolio with this acquisition.

news.title: Rajkot: FIR filed against builder for sale of encumbered flats
news.para: Hetal Tilala, a teacher, has accused Viren Sindhav of fraud. She bought a flat in Shivay Apartments in 2018. Sindhav allegedly mortgaged the building for a loan in 2019. Tilala discovered this in 2025 via a legal notice. Mandavrayji Credit Co-operative Society sought loan recovery. Sindhav admitted to the loan but claimed partial repayment.

news.title: Fallout of arrests over illegal Vasai buildings: Just one town planner left, files pile up
news.para: The arrest of two top Vasai-Virar civic officials in a money laundering case tied to illegal construction has paralyzed the town planning department. With staff shortages and pending approvals, the civic body faces significant revenue loss. The department is struggling to manage daily operations and complete the development plan, prompting a request for additional officers.

news.title: Goa government to regularise 20-point plots, district collectors can issue sanads
news.para: The revenue department is set to regularize residential plots allotted to weaker sections under the 20-Point Programme, resolving issues with clearances and financial aid. District collectors can now issue Class I sanads directly. Plots with dwellings will be converted to Class I occupancy upon premium payment, while vacant plots revert to the government.

news.title: Hong Kong allows cheaper home purchases for investment visas
news.para: Hong Kong is reducing the investment threshold for residential property purchases under its investor visa program to HK$30 million, aiming to stimulate its struggling property market. This adjustment, announced by Chief Executive John Lee, seeks to attract more investment amid oversupply and economic challenges.

news.title: Court ‘crossed limits’, says Bombay HC, gives back 16-acre plot to builder
news.para: Bombay High Court intervened in a land dispute near Dahisar. The court reinstated a magistrate's order favoring Romell Housing. This order declared Romell Housing in possession of the land in April 2017. The court directed the receiver to hand over the plot to Romell Housing.

news.title: Tamil Nadu Housing Board pitches commercial hubs cheaper than private rentals
news.para: Tamil Nadu Housing Board is offering commercial complexes across Chennai at budget-friendly rates, nearly 20% cheaper than private rentals, attracting government departments like EPFO and GST. Seven complexes in prime locations with metro connectivity are proving attractive. TNHB seeks private sector participation for upcoming projects in Peters Colony, Arumbakkam, and Ashok Nagar, with 70% of available space already rented.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Ambuja Cements & JSW Cement to mediate 'kawach' trademark dispute amicably
news.para: The Delhi High Court has directed Ambuja Cements and JSW Cement to engage in mediation to resolve their trademark infringement dispute concerning the "kawach" trademark. Ambuja Cements alleges that JSW Cement's "Jal Kavach" cement infringes upon its registered "Ambuja Kawach" trademark, used since 2020 for water-repellent cement.

news.title: Ghaziabad property prices set to go up as Uttar Pradesh proposes 40% hike in circle rates
news.para: Ghaziabad is poised for a property price surge as the district administration plans to increase circle rates by up to 40%. Residential plots may see a 5-15% rise, while flats in large townships could jump by 35-40%. Commercial and industrial properties are also slated for significant hikes, impacting property transactions due to increased stamp duty and registration fees.

news.title: Kerala government assures smooth fund flow for Life Mission houses
news.para: Kerala's Life Mission project has provided 4,62,412 families with completed houses since 2017, with 1,33,124 more under construction, aiming to reach over six lakh beneficiaries by the government's term end. Minister Rajesh addressed assembly concerns about funding delays, highlighting the state's Rs 4 lakh contribution per house, significantly higher than the central PM Awas Yojana.

news.title: Developer, seven others booked for selling mortgaged flats in Dehu Road area
news.para: A developer in Dehu, along with seven others, has been booked for allegedly defrauding eight home buyers of ₹1.84 crore. They sold flats in a Malinagar housing complex that were already mortgaged to a credit society. The developer failed to disclose the loan to MahaRERA, violating regulations and leading to a police investigation for cheating and breach of trust.

news.title: SC directs states, UTs to strengthen real estate bodies
news.para: The Supreme Court has directed states and Union Territories to bolster their RERA authorities with adequate staffing, infrastructure, and legal expertise. These directives aim to prevent RERA bodies from becoming ineffective and ensure timely order implementation.

news.title: HC refuses relief to Ansal properties, says HRERA penalties must be faced despite insolvency
news.para: The Punjab and Haryana High Court has upheld interim penalty orders issued by HRERA against Ansal Properties for non-compliance with RERA Act, stating that insolvency proceedings do not exempt the company from statutory obligations.

news.title: Builder booked for cheating bank of ₹16.49 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Yash builders and its proprietor, Paras Dedhia, face accusations of cheating and criminal breach of trust after Axis Bank filed a complaint regarding a ₹16.49 crore loan for the Yash Signature project. Dedhia allegedly defaulted on repayments, failed to open an escrow account, and sold mortgaged properties without the bank's consent, leading to the account being declared NPA.
